    <howToApply>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Applications for the Trust should be returned by 8th February, alongside: </p>
<ul>
<li>References from the first named referee on your application form
<ul>
<li>First reference must be academic</li>
<li>Second reference can be academic or character based and will be contacted if you are shortlisted</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>A personal statement including: 
<ul>
<li>Your reasoning for choosing your career in which women are under represented</li>
<li>Clear explanation using statistics and relevant data to show that women are under represented in your field of work and study</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Projected income and expenditure for the proposed academic year
<ul>
<li>Should illustrate funding from the Trust will cover a deficit</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Unfortunately, the Trust is unable to accept retrospective awards. Therefore, you must be a registered student in the year the funding is paid to you. </p>
<p>The Trust can only offer a limited number of awards each year. Consequently, please make sure that you and your course of study fit the eligibility criteria carefully before submitting an application. </p>]]></Value>
    </howToApply>
    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW258539821 BCX0">The Hilda Marindale Educational Trust offers grants to female identifying British Nationals who are studying a course with the purposes of following a profession or career where women are underrepresented. Grants of up to £3,000 are offered. Please note, students who received an award from the trust the previous academic year are unable to apply for a second consecutive year.</span> </p>]]></Value>
    </introduction>
